column5: Anyone going to fish Fishmasters walleye tourney this Saturday .I am just wondering if any other OFC,ers were going
im gonna try and make it.

If you plan to fish right up to the dam, make your own anchors that you dont mind losing, and bring a few. I get my anchor stuck everytime I go out, and have lost several. Can be very dangerous to get it back at times too, as you are 5 feet away from the dam  pulling on the rope hoping it will get unstuck. Be careful.
I'll be there trying to go two for two,,,!! Always a good day out on the river...ohh  and i'm sure there's a limit on how close you can fish to the dam. Never got my anchor stuck once!
I'll be on the Grand Saturday but upstream a little targetting smallies between Conestogo and Bridgeport in my kayak.

who is hosting the tourney?what are the areas,is obviously on the grand?because I never lost an anchor at dunville even at the edge of the dam.Never been told of a tourney.any repllies would be great.thanks
i will be there finished 3rd last year hoping to improve steve runs a great tourny its a good time
thanks roy for the input,ill be there.thanks for the input, I launch from there on ocaasions.Hope to see some ofnrs there on saturday.Ill be with my buddy and my 20ft bowrider.
I'll be there.  I hope I get into a few!
